{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DWAYNE, slovenly, 35, with a walrus mustache, looks up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm looking for Investor's Center?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE
{DIALOGUE}: That's us, hey.
{DIALOGUE}: Dwayne.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{META_DATA}: (as they shake hands)
{DIALOGUE}: Jordan Belfort, I called earlier.
{DIALOGUE}: I was a broker with Rothschild.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dwayne motions Jordan to a seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nearby, a Broker in ratty Keds, TOBY WELCH, is screaming into his phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBY WELCH
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tellin' you, this stock is goin' up!
{DIALOGUE}: ... Cause I know, okay?!
{DIALOGUE}: ... I have inside information!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan looks at him, appalled at what he's hearing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Where are your quotrons?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE
{DIALOGUE}: No quotrons, we sell off the pink sheets -- penny stocks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dwayne slides Jordan a large thin book; its pages are literally pink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He explains as Jordan flips the pages:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Company don't have enough capital to be listed on NASDAQ, their shares trade here.
{META_DATA}: (points to the book)
{DIALOGUE}: Like these guys, Aerotyne?
{DIALOGUE}: They make radar detectors out of a garage in Dubuque.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Six cents a share?
{DIALOGUE}: Who buys this crap?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE
{DIALOGUE}: Schmucks mostly.
{DIALOGUE}: Mailmen, plumbers, people thinking they can get rich quick.
{DIALOGUE}: They answer our ads, Popular Mechanics, Hustler.
{DIALOGUE}: 14.
{DIALOGUE}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: The spread on these is huge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE
{DIALOGUE}: So's your commission, that's the point.
{DIALOGUE}: Blue chips stocks you get what, one percent?
{DIALOGUE}: Pink sheets are fifty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Wait a second.
{DIALOGUE}: You're telling me if I sell two thousand dollars worth of stock, my commission is a thousand bucks?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DWAYNE
{DIALOGUE}: Technically, yeah, but not even the biggest schmuck buys two thousand dollars of this shit.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 28 INT. INVESTOR'S CENTER - (LATER THAT) DAY (DEC '87)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As others Brokers bark into phones, Jordan sits, phone cradled in his shoulder, making notes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few beats, then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Fleming, good morning, Jordan Belfort with Investor's Center in New York City.
{DIALOGUE}: You recently responded to one of our ads...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few of the other Brokers glance over, eavesdropping.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The reason I'm calling is that an extremely exciting investment opportunity crossed my desk today.
{DIALOGUE}: Typically our firm recommends no more than five stocks per year: this is one of them...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few more Brokers look over...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Aerotyne International is a cutting edge tech firm out of the Midwest, awaiting imminent patent approval on a new generation of radar equipment...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now all the Brokers listen in rapt attention.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 15.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: -- so if Aerotyne's shares rise to only a dollar -- and our research indicates they could go much, much higher -- your profit on a mere three thousand dollar investment would be upwards of fifty thousand... That's right, you could pay off your mortgage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seconds tick by; an eternity, then he starts writing:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Four thousand dollars, will that be check or money order?
{DIALOGUE}: ... Thank you, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan hangs up, scrawls out a "buy" ticket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Just like that I made two grand.
{DIALOGUE}: The other guys looked at me like I'd just discovered fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toby Welch and the other cave-Brokers stare at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBY WELCH
{DIALOGUE}: How'd you fuckin' do that?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 29 INT. INVESTOR'S CENTER - (ANOTHER) DAY (FEB `88)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan sits at his desk in mid-pitch, totally focused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: It's a rock-solid company, sir, it's the next Microsoft... Six thousand.
{DIALOGUE}: Terrific.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Jordan continues talking, wrapping up the sale...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Though I knew I was selling garbage, within twelve weeks I was making a fortune.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as he starts scrawling out a buy ticket...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And as a wise man once told me, my only responsibility was to put meat on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a 1988 Jaguar, parked outside a diner... 16.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 30 INT. KACANDES DINER - BAYSIDE - DAY (JUN `88)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wearing a suit, Jordan sits in a booth reading the Wall Street Journal as a WAITRESS serves the food.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DONNIE AZOFF, preppy-looking, 25, with horn-rims and bright white teeth approaches from the takeout counter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: That your Jag in the lot?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Nice ride.
{DIALOGUE}: Donnie Azoff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Jordan Belfort.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: I've seen it around.
{DIALOGUE}: We live in the same building.
{DIALOGUE}: Twelfth floor?
{META_DATA}: (Jordan nods)
{DIALOGUE}: What do you do, bro?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Stock broker.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Kids furniture, me and my brother- in-law.
{DIALOGUE}: Making any money?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Seventy grand last month.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Get the fuck out.
{DIALOGUE}: You made seventy grand in one month.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Seventy two actually.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Donnie studies him, isn't sure if he's full of shit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Tell you what.
{DIALOGUE}: You show me a pay stub with $72,000 on it, I'm quitting my job right now and coming to work with you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Jordan retrieves his briefcase to find a paystub --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 30A SCENE 30A OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 30B As Jordan hands Donnie his paystub and sure enough, it's north of seventy-two k. 17.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Holy shit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan watches as Donnie crosses to a pay phone and dials.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And he did quit his job, which I thought was a little weird.
{DIALOGUE}: I mean I had just met this fucking guy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few beats, then into phone:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Yo Paulie, it's Donnie... Yeah, listen, I quit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan studies Donnie as he continues his conversation...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: There were other things about him too, like his phosphorescent white teeth and the fact that he wore horn rims with clear lenses to look more Waspy.
{DIALOGUE}: He also married his first cousin --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 31 SCENE 31 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 32 INT. BAR - DAY (JUN `88)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan sits in mid-conversation with Donnie over beers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: No problem, if we have a kid who's a retard, we'll just leave it on the steps of some institution.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as they continue drinking...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: He was also a closet drug fiend.
{DIALOGUE}: I'd known him less than a week before he talked me into smoking crack.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 33 EXT. BACK OF BAR - DAY (JUN `88)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan and Donnie get high.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Donnie holds a flame under a crack pipe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 18.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: The weird thing was when he'd do crack, his face would contort into this bizarre, frozen mask like the Phantom of the Opera.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Donnie does a hit of crack; his jaw twitches, then his facial muscles contort, locking up like a stroke victim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a few beats, he hands the pipe to Jordan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DONNIE
{DIALOGUE}: You now, take a hit!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan takes a deep hit and holds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat, then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Omigod, I fuckin' love you!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I knew I had to make him my partner.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 34 INT. INVESTOR'S CENTER - DAY (SEP `88)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan looks on as Donnie works the phone like a madman.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Which turned out to be a great move - Donnie was a fast learner who transitioned into the penny stock business quickly.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 35 EXT. STRATTON OAKMONT I - AUTO SHOP - DAY (SEP `88)
