{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 47 INT. STRATTON OAKMONT I - AUTO BODY SHOP - REAR - NIGHT
{META_DATA}: (MAR `90)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera PUSHES IN on Jordan as he stands before a large dry erase board.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: But what if they didn't sound like jerk-offs?
{DIALOGUE}: What if I took this bunch of nincompoops and molded them in my own image?
{DIALOGUE}: I reinvented the company, gave it a new image, a new name.
{DIALOGUE}: Something patrician, blue-blooded, something that reeked of tradition and anti- semitism.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as his Brokers settle in to folding chairs--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Gentlemen, welcome to Stratton Oakmont.
{DIALOGUE}: The clients we've gone after in the past -- they're done.
{DIALOGUE}: We will now target exclusively the wealthiest one percent of Americans.
{DIALOGUE}: The methods we've used -- over.
{DIALOGUE}: Loud, obnoxious sales hype is worthless with these people.
{DIALOGUE}: 23.
{DIALOGUE}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: In military terms it's like carpet- bombing -- noisy, menacing and only marginally effective.
{DIALOGUE}: As Stratton brokers you will be laser- guided smart-bombs aimed at high- priority targets.
{DIALOGUE}: You will establish an initial relationship with your clients selling only blue chip stocks -- then and only then will you attempt to sell the pink sheets, where the real money is.
{DIALOGUE}: Now the key to every sale is this:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan writes the word "URGENCY" on the board.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: No one buys stock unless he thinks it's going up and going up now.
{DIALOGUE}: You must convince your client to buy before the takeover happens, before the lawsuit is settled, before the patent is granted.
{DIALOGUE}: If he says I'll think about it and call you back, it's over, you're dead!
{DIALOGUE}: No one calls back!
{DIALOGUE}: So you have to create urgency --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 48 INT. STRATTON OAKMONT I - AUTO SHOP BULLPEN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With Stratton Oakmont signage visible in the b.g., Jordan is on speakerphone with a potential CLIENT, the other Brokers listening in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: --and once Kodak settles the lawsuit, institutions will be permitted to buy their shares in large blocks again.
