{DIALOGUE}: Didn't want to be a broker, wanted to be an environmental scientist or something, he had a student loan debts up to his eyeballs.
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway, his mom gets sick, all they can afford is third-rate care.
{DIALOGUE}: Some of us got together, made an investment on his behalf and -- boom -- overnight everything changes, she's seeing the best doctors in the country.
{DIALOGUE}: Sadly, didn't work out, she passed but still: having the power to do that makes all the other bullshit worth while.
