{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: For the next six hours, I came up with a list.
{DIALOGUE}: Friends, enemies, business associates, anybody who'd ever known me or taken so much as a stock tip.
{DIALOGUE}: The first name on the list was Donnie's.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as Jordan heaves a huge sigh, we're suddenly...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 231 INT. FBI OFFICE - DAY (OCT `98)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Denham tapes a recorder to Jordan's inner thigh, runs a microphone wire up his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Hughes watches.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: Talk normally, breathe normally, within five minutes you'll forget you even have it on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan nods, buttons up his shirt.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 232 INT. STRATTON OAKMONT III - BULLPEN - DAY (OCT `98)
