{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 247 EXT. MINIMUM C PRISON - DAY (SPRING 2000)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tennis ball hits pavement and WE PAN UP TO JORDAN, in prison fatigues but playing doubles with three other PRISONERS, all white middle-aged EXECUTIVE TYPES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, just out.
{DIALOGUE}: What is that, forty-thirty?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the game continues, Jordan serving, the CAMERA PULLS UP TO SEE THE WHOLE PRISON YARD: one group of inmates does Tai Chi while another has formed a book club.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: For a brief, fleeting moment, I'd forgotten I was rich and lived in America.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLACK OUT.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 248 INT. HOTEL BANQUET HALL - EARLY 2000'S - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON A MOVIE SCREEN: DIFFERENT INTERVIEWS...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AFRICAN KID
{DIALOGUE}: I watch him speak and what he says is motivational about life.
{DIALOGUE}: He tells about life and how you can be more rich.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHINESE KID
{DIALOGUE}: He is going to teach us how to be successful, how to set our goals.
{DIALOGUE}: 136.
{DIALOGUE}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: INDIAN KID
{DIALOGUE}: I will build my future by using Jordan Belfort as my mentor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MEXICAN KID
{DIALOGUE}: Choosing what is good from him and being a millionaire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two hundred people attend Jordan's "Straight Line Persuasion" seminar, watching a massive screen (on which these KIDS have appeared).
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON-SCREEN: THE "JB" LOGO APPEARS, FOLLOWED BY CLIPS OF JORDAN giving seminars in different locations (see addendum below), edited in with footage of looming economic uncertainties.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then: a MAN WITH A MIC steps out...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MAN WITH A MIC Ladies and gentlemen, please join me in welcoming to Auckland, New Zealand... Mr. Jordan Belfort!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BIG APPLAUSE as Jordan takes the stage, waving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This might go on a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: If so, there COULD be TITLES:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan Belfort spent 22 months in federal prison and paid $100,000,000 in fines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEN:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His cellmate was, no fucking joke, Tommy Chong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEN:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Since his release, he's become a multi-millionaire again as a motivational speaker.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When the applause finally dies down...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...Jordan doesn't speak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instead he walks down to the front row of his audience, studying faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Takes a pen from his coat and offers it to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sell me this pen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Kiwi, embarrassed, takes a moment, then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIWI IN AUDIENCE
{DIALOGUE}: Well, it's a good pen, it's a ballpoint --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jordan takes the pen back with a smile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hands it to the next person.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 137.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Wolf of Wall Street Buff Revised Pages 3/5/13
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sell me this pen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the next person tries...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE RAKE ALONGSIDE HIS AUDIENCE, transfixed, desperate for Jordan's knowledge, desperate to be molded, to be rich...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JORDAN (O.S.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Sell me this pen...Sell me this pen... Sell me this pen...Sell me this pen...
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT.
